  "explanation": "While the defendant committed a serious breach of fiduciary duty by embezzling $25,000 from their employer, several mitigating factors strongly influence this sentence. The defendant has no prior criminal record, the crime was non-violent in nature, and partial restitution has already been made, demonstrating remorse and a genuine effort to make the victim whole. A lengthy prison sentence would impede the defendant's ability to earn an income and pay back the remaining stolen funds. However, to account for the serious abuse of professional trust and to serve as a sufficient deterrent, a brief period of incarceration is necessary before transitioning to probation and mandatory full restitution.",
  "verdict": 3
}
